I've seen this a few times now. Does it mean "built p10bmc out of master" or something else? CI will build the p10bmc system out of master so I don't think this is neededd

In master CI it may not be building p10bmc?
I think it is somehow missing to build extensions folder, so any compile errors in that folder are not getting detected, doing an explicit build of p10bmc out of master to verify that.
I see, https://jenkins.openbmc.org/job/ci-openbmc/ will build p10bmc but not until this is merged and in a bump so def good idea to build it on it's own.
If we're starting fresh here, be good to address TODO's vs. just copying into new class.
EpochTime is needed and that being used by BMCweb to show the timestamp, just remove the todo?
Getting rid of epoch in the new base class, and the clients should get the value from the completed time in the progress interface

This is the earlier commit

https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/+/42932/

If this or multiple level of inheritance are not employed, there will be heavy code duplication
This commit was not included in this chain. looks like still in wip.
This commit cannot be included because this design is not approved

Since you don't have any design document published to reviewers to see the final goal and benefit with approach , need either class diagram or the code to get better understanding on your code and advantage with this approach with use cases.

What I understood is, the preference is for smaller commits explaining the changes than the design document. I think these commits are smaller and explain the scope.
Including the class diagram in the commit message is difficult because always not able to get to 72char length
 
but I didn't get the meaning of the code to understand, do you mean the complete code of the refactor?

Openbmc process of code refactoring is 
 - either share the design or send a mail to mailing list by providing the background and the high level design direction.
   This will help both reviewers and maintainers to get bigger picture on design direction.

Eg :  refer the below mail which provides high level summary and  
https://lists.ozlabs.org/pipermail/openbmc/2019-November/019664.html and https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-certificate-manager/+/28295 .
This could be an old process, but will send a mail with the points about refactoring
Please use some common label to group all refactoring commits. Also point to the commit message which talks about the refcatoring scope/design direction.

Will update common label.
Each commit explains the scope of the change
